1
00:01:34,010 --> 00:01:35,303
IN SURGERY, SONG HA-YOUNG

2
00:01:40,475 --> 00:01:42,268
Luckily, he's out of the woods for now.

3
00:01:42,352 --> 00:01:44,562
Once we wrap up, we'll move him to the ICU

4
00:01:44,646 --> 00:01:46,898
and monitor his recovery.

5
00:01:47,941 --> 00:01:48,983
Thank you.

6
00:01:49,067 --> 00:01:51,402
Thank you. Good work.

7
00:01:55,490 --> 00:01:57,200
I should've taken better care of him.

8
00:01:57,784 --> 00:01:58,910
It's all right.

9
00:02:00,036 --> 00:02:02,038
I know he's going to wake up soon.

10
00:02:02,122 --> 00:02:03,206
He will.

11
00:02:10,588 --> 00:02:12,006
<i>Was I six years old then?</i>

12
00:02:13,174 --> 00:02:15,927
I went to an amusement park
with my mother on Children's Day.

13
00:02:16,427 --> 00:02:18,429
That was the first time I saw a dead body.

14
00:02:18,513 --> 00:02:20,223
You were pretty young.

15
00:02:21,391 --> 00:02:23,101
The body was in the water.

16
00:02:23,768 --> 00:02:26,146
<i>When I saw her face,</i>

17
00:02:26,229 --> 00:02:28,106
<i>she didn't scare me.</i>

18
00:02:28,189 --> 00:02:29,774
<i>She just looked very lonely.</i>

19
00:02:30,859 --> 00:02:32,861
<i>"She must have been terrified."</i>

20
00:02:33,486 --> 00:02:35,530
<i>"She must've been lonely and in pain."</i>

21
00:02:35,613 --> 00:02:37,115
<i>That's what crossed my mind.</i>

22
00:02:38,825 --> 00:02:41,494
So I wanted to reach out to hold her hand.

23
00:02:44,706 --> 00:02:46,374
But I couldn't do that back then.

24
00:02:52,422 --> 00:02:54,299
Just like what you've been doing,

25
00:02:56,050 --> 00:02:59,012
you probably did something
to help the woman back then.

26
00:03:09,272 --> 00:03:12,317
<i>The Southwest Case serial killer,
Nam Ki-Tae,</i>

27
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:15,403
<i>said he'd kill again if he were released,</i>

28
00:03:15,486 --> 00:03:16,988
<i>which shocked the public.</i>

29
00:03:17,739 --> 00:03:20,867
We should hang men like him
in the middle of Gwanghwamun

30
00:03:20,950 --> 00:03:23,912
and stone them to death.

31
00:03:23,995 --> 00:03:27,624
Why do people want to keep him alive?
I really don't get it.

32
00:03:27,707 --> 00:03:30,710
What he did was inhumane.
He doesn't deserve human rights.

33
00:03:30,793 --> 00:03:34,297
Sir, I'm sorry,
but could you turn that off please?

34
00:03:34,380 --> 00:03:36,049
It's giving me a headache.

35
00:03:36,132 --> 00:03:38,551
Right. Sure.

36
00:03:39,177 --> 00:03:41,512
This news isn't that pleasant
to listen to.

37
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:17,859
TOJUNG-DONG, ANYANG, GYEONGGI PROVINCE

38
00:05:20,528 --> 00:05:21,654
What?

39
00:05:23,072 --> 00:05:24,574
I'm in Tojung-dong right now.

40
00:05:26,117 --> 00:05:28,077
I need to check out a missing person case.

41
00:05:29,829 --> 00:05:30,872
I'll be there later.

42
00:05:30,955 --> 00:05:35,168
HERO KARAOKE BAR

43
00:05:37,837 --> 00:05:40,298
-Excuse me.
-We're not open yet.

44
00:05:40,381 --> 00:05:41,424
I see.

45
00:05:42,675 --> 00:05:44,969
-I'm from the police.
-Hello.

46
00:05:55,146 --> 00:05:57,023
<i>You're my lady lady</i>

47
00:05:57,106 --> 00:05:59,025
<i>I can't live without you</i>

48
00:05:59,108 --> 00:06:03,446
<i>The only thing I need in my life is you</i>

49
00:06:06,616 --> 00:06:07,784
Are you having fun?

50
00:06:07,867 --> 00:06:09,410
I got bored of waiting.

51
00:06:11,954 --> 00:06:13,164
Brief me.

52
00:06:15,291 --> 00:06:16,667
I told you over the phone.

53
00:06:17,668 --> 00:06:19,504
So she left after singing here.

54
00:06:19,587 --> 00:06:21,798
-And then she can't be reached.
-Right.

55
00:06:21,881 --> 00:06:23,883
She left alone without a customer?

56
00:06:23,966 --> 00:06:24,801
Right.

57
00:06:25,593 --> 00:06:27,053
-That's it?
-Right.

58
00:06:27,136 --> 00:06:29,889
A woman in her forties
was having fun with her customer here.

59
00:06:29,972 --> 00:06:32,141
And she left before the customer,

60
00:06:32,225 --> 00:06:34,102
and she can't be reached ever since.

61
00:06:34,185 --> 00:06:35,478
Is that really it?

62
00:06:35,561 --> 00:06:36,771
Right.

63
00:06:38,564 --> 00:06:40,191
Come on.

64
00:06:40,274 --> 00:06:42,068
Chief Park.

65
00:06:42,151 --> 00:06:43,611
I came all the way here.

66
00:06:43,694 --> 00:06:45,530
You should have gotten a lead.

67
00:06:45,613 --> 00:06:47,031
I didn't ask you to come here.

68
00:06:47,115 --> 00:06:49,158
-You came here on your own.
-Damn you.

69
00:06:49,742 --> 00:06:51,911
You want me to report this

70
00:06:51,994 --> 00:06:53,287
as criminal intelligence?

71
00:06:53,996 --> 00:06:55,123
You do it. I'm out.

72
00:06:55,206 --> 00:06:59,377
Another woman from a different karaoke bar
went missing in February.

73
00:07:00,670 --> 00:07:01,671
What?

74
00:07:01,754 --> 00:07:02,630
MISSING PERSON

75
00:07:02,713 --> 00:07:04,006
Two cases?

76
00:07:05,842 --> 00:07:06,843
Yes.

77
00:07:08,094 --> 00:07:10,471
In February, a female worker

78
00:07:10,555 --> 00:07:12,181
at a karaoke bar in Suwon went missing.

79
00:07:12,265 --> 00:07:15,101
-But that case hasn't been filed yet.
-Why not?

80
00:07:15,184 --> 00:07:18,438
A lot of these workers often go AWOL
and move to another karaoke bar.

81
00:07:18,521 --> 00:07:19,480
I guess that's why.

82
00:07:19,564 --> 00:07:22,567
But how did you come across this case?
This wasn't filed.

83
00:07:22,650 --> 00:07:24,068
When I was on this case,

84
00:07:24,152 --> 00:07:26,446
my friend who worked
at a karaoke bar in Suwon said

85
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:31,409
a worker there
went missing out of the blue like this.

86
00:07:36,372 --> 00:07:37,582
What's your take on this?

87
00:07:37,665 --> 00:07:40,209
What I think doesn't matter.

88
00:07:40,918 --> 00:07:42,545
I'm just a cop.

89
00:07:42,628 --> 00:07:44,297
I investigate when I get the order.

90
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:45,840
And I don't when there's none.

91
00:07:45,923 --> 00:07:47,592
You're a detective. You have no hunches?

92
00:07:47,675 --> 00:07:50,553
Show me that you're at least trying
to open this case.

93
00:07:50,636 --> 00:07:53,139
There was a time

94
00:07:53,222 --> 00:07:54,724
when I had to pay a hefty price

95
00:07:54,807 --> 00:07:56,309
because of my hunches.

96
00:07:57,268 --> 00:07:59,729
So I'm careful with everything.

97
00:07:59,812 --> 00:08:02,064
-Okay. You can leave now.
-Okay.

98
00:08:03,232 --> 00:08:05,359
SUPERINTENDENT HEO GIL-PYO

99
00:08:05,443 --> 00:08:08,488
Well, both of the missing women

100
00:08:08,571 --> 00:08:10,448
were in the same line of work.

101
00:08:10,531 --> 00:08:12,074
I couldn't find any connections

102
00:08:12,158 --> 00:08:13,784
other than their profession.

103
00:08:14,368 --> 00:08:15,369
Thenâ€¦

104
00:08:16,162 --> 00:08:18,956
is it possible that
there was no motive behind these cases?

105
00:08:19,540 --> 00:08:20,750
Is that your hunch?

106
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:23,669
Well, every detective has a hunch.

107
00:08:25,379 --> 00:08:26,464
Go.

108
00:08:37,850 --> 00:08:38,893
This way.

109
00:08:40,728 --> 00:08:41,604
Hello.

110
00:08:41,687 --> 00:08:43,397
YEONGTONG-GU,
SUWON, GYEONGGI PROVINCE

111
00:08:43,481 --> 00:08:45,274
SHIN MI-JUNG'S HOUSE

112
00:08:48,653 --> 00:08:50,988
You guys still haven't found her?

113
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:54,242
Maybe something really happened to her

114
00:08:54,325 --> 00:08:56,118
if even you guys can't find her.

115
00:08:56,202 --> 00:08:57,662
That's not necessarily true.

116
00:08:57,745 --> 00:08:59,247
We're here to check a few things.

117
00:08:59,330 --> 00:09:00,414
Why come here twice

118
00:09:00,498 --> 00:09:01,624
if this wasn't serious?

119
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:04,919
Did she pay rent monthly?

120
00:09:05,545 --> 00:09:06,546
She paid me monthly.

121
00:09:09,924 --> 00:09:12,927
If you couldn't reach her since February,

122
00:09:13,010 --> 00:09:15,346
she must be behind on rent
for three months.

123
00:09:16,097 --> 00:09:18,307
Yes. But I can just deduct her rent

124
00:09:18,391 --> 00:09:20,810
from the initial deposit she made.

125
00:09:20,893 --> 00:09:22,687
I just hope she's okay.

126
00:09:22,770 --> 00:09:25,356
So no one came after our visit?

127
00:09:25,439 --> 00:09:26,524
Hey.

128
00:09:27,358 --> 00:09:28,442
Gosh.

129
00:09:29,235 --> 00:09:30,278
She's been my tenant

130
00:09:30,361 --> 00:09:31,654
for the past three years.

131
00:09:31,737 --> 00:09:32,947
And I haven't seen her

132
00:09:33,030 --> 00:09:34,407
bringing people here.

133
00:09:34,490 --> 00:09:37,034
She even stayed here during the holidays.

134
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:39,579
HERO KARAOKE BAR

135
00:09:42,707 --> 00:09:44,625
SHIN MI-JUNG, NO FAMILY, CASE NOT FILED

136
00:09:47,086 --> 00:09:49,130
MISSING PERSON

137
00:09:49,213 --> 00:09:50,840
SING SING KARAOKE
HOSTESSES ALWAYS AVAILABLE

138
00:10:00,099 --> 00:10:01,392
Yes, come in.

139
00:10:07,148 --> 00:10:08,774
Please call Song Ha-young.

140
00:10:09,859 --> 00:10:10,735
Inspector Song?

141
00:10:10,818 --> 00:10:13,529
I read the article and heard stories.

142
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:16,449
He has a knack for identifying
connections between cases.

143
00:10:18,951 --> 00:10:19,952
Hey.

144
00:10:20,536 --> 00:10:22,997
You really don't think
it's a missing person's case?

145
00:10:23,956 --> 00:10:26,709
Well, we have no concrete proof yet,

146
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:29,253
but my hunch says otherwise.

147
00:10:30,796 --> 00:10:34,008
If that's your hunch, it's probably right.

148
00:10:42,475 --> 00:10:44,810
Mr. Heo, to what do I owe
the pleasure of this call?

149
00:10:44,894 --> 00:10:46,687
<i>Hey, how have you been?</i>

150
00:10:46,771 --> 00:10:48,731
It took you this long to think of me?

151
00:10:48,814 --> 00:10:50,524
I just faxed something over to you.

152
00:10:50,608 --> 00:10:53,027
<i>It's a missing person's case.
Can you look into it?</i>

153
00:10:53,110 --> 00:10:55,279
Of course,
you wouldn't call me for no reason.

154
00:10:55,363 --> 00:10:57,740
A missing karaoke bar employee?
Is this the case?

155
00:10:57,823 --> 00:11:00,076
No. We did receive a report for that one.

156
00:11:00,159 --> 00:11:02,119
Apparently, there's an unreported case.

157
00:11:02,203 --> 00:11:03,412
"Apparently"?

158
00:11:04,497 --> 00:11:07,708
The person has no family or friends,
and no one can reach her.

159
00:11:07,792 --> 00:11:08,793
What about this case?

160
00:11:08,876 --> 00:11:10,628
Both missing women

161
00:11:12,338 --> 00:11:13,547
worked at karaoke bars.

162
00:11:13,631 --> 00:11:16,967
<i>When the Special Crime Squad
was all lost, you guys said</i>

163
00:11:17,051 --> 00:11:19,678
<i>cases with more than
two common things may be connected.</i>

164
00:11:19,762 --> 00:11:23,682
These could be like the motiveless crimes
you mentioned.

165
00:11:23,766 --> 00:11:25,434
Can you go check with Inspector Song?

166
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:26,477
Ha-young can't go.

167
00:11:27,395 --> 00:11:28,896
This is how you treat me now?

168
00:11:28,979 --> 00:11:31,232
You're hurting my feelings here.

169
00:11:31,315 --> 00:11:32,358
I'll go and check.

170
00:11:32,942 --> 00:11:36,362
Right, everyone says
your team is in high demand now.

171
00:11:36,445 --> 00:11:38,572
I'll look into it and call you back.

172
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:40,366
Okay.

173
00:11:42,118 --> 00:11:44,495
Was that Superintendent Heo
at Gyeonggi Police Agency?

174
00:11:44,578 --> 00:11:45,704
Yes.

175
00:11:46,622 --> 00:11:48,999
I guess he hasn't heard
about Inspector Song yet.

176
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:50,543
He's at Gyeonggi Agency now,

177
00:11:50,626 --> 00:11:52,753
so he wouldn't know
unless he looked into it.

178
00:11:54,088 --> 00:11:56,340
This is a missing person's case.

179
00:11:56,424 --> 00:11:59,385
Let's check the area, her movements,
and the time of the incident.

180
00:11:59,468 --> 00:12:00,678
Yes, sir.

181
00:12:11,605 --> 00:12:12,898
You're doing great.

182
00:12:14,525 --> 00:12:15,901
Let's try that one more time.

183
00:12:23,284 --> 00:12:25,661
<i>Neuroparalysis?</i>

184
00:12:25,744 --> 00:12:28,330
When the fractures occurred
at the time of the accident,

185
00:12:28,414 --> 00:12:31,292
some of the nerves around the bones
were damaged.

186
00:12:31,375 --> 00:12:34,211
Thankfully, he can move his toes a little,

187
00:12:34,295 --> 00:12:37,423
and there isn't a complete
loss of sensation,

188
00:12:37,506 --> 00:12:40,301
so I'd say it's partial paralysis.

189
00:12:40,384 --> 00:12:41,760
<i>In cases like this,</i>

190
00:12:41,844 --> 00:12:44,889
<i>he could recover
through rehabilitative therapy.</i>

191
00:12:44,972 --> 00:12:47,349
<i>The Seoul Metropolitan Police Agency</i>

192
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:49,810
<i>transferred gang members who had been</i>

193
00:12:49,894 --> 00:12:51,979
<i>embezzling cash through an illegal casino</i>

194
00:12:52,062 --> 00:12:54,106
<i>to the prosecution.</i>

195
00:12:54,190 --> 00:12:56,901
We wrapped up another case.

196
00:12:56,984 --> 00:12:58,360
Good work, everyone.

197
00:12:58,444 --> 00:12:59,695
How about a team dinner?

198
00:12:59,778 --> 00:13:02,239
You want to drink, don't you?
Sit down already.

199
00:13:02,323 --> 00:13:03,824
The case isn't closed

200
00:13:03,908 --> 00:13:05,493
until the trial is over.

201
00:13:05,576 --> 00:13:08,120
I told them to contact us
if they need more evidence.

202
00:13:08,204 --> 00:13:09,413
Okay.

203
00:13:09,997 --> 00:13:12,708
<i>The gift certificates they received
were usedâ€¦</i>

204
00:13:12,791 --> 00:13:16,295
Right. Shouldn't we visit Inspector Song
in the hospital?

205
00:13:16,378 --> 00:13:19,798
We haven't seen him
since he moved to the general ward, right?

206
00:13:19,882 --> 00:13:20,925
That's right.

207
00:13:22,801 --> 00:13:26,472
GYEONGGI PROVINCIAL POLICE AGENCY

208
00:13:33,521 --> 00:13:34,897
Look at you.

209
00:13:36,315 --> 00:13:38,442
Salute, Superintendent Heo Gil-pyo.

210
00:13:39,902 --> 00:13:41,695
Did you really come alone?

211
00:13:41,779 --> 00:13:44,073
Why? Am I not good enough?

212
00:13:44,156 --> 00:13:46,700
I trained Korea's first criminal profiler.

213
00:13:46,784 --> 00:13:47,743
I'm in high demand.

214
00:13:47,826 --> 00:13:49,662
Goodness. Don't be so difficult.

215
00:13:49,745 --> 00:13:51,580
This is so cool.

216
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:55,125
Oh, there he is.

217
00:13:55,209 --> 00:13:56,877
This is Chief Park
of the Serious Crime Unit.

218
00:13:56,961 --> 00:13:58,379
You know him, right?

219
00:13:58,462 --> 00:14:00,464
-Yes, we've met.
-It's been a while.

220
00:14:00,548 --> 00:14:01,840
Take a seat.

221
00:14:03,968 --> 00:14:06,720
Are you in charge of this case?

222
00:14:06,804 --> 00:14:09,181
No, Anyang Police Station is in charge,

223
00:14:10,015 --> 00:14:11,267
but it's a little strange.

224
00:14:11,350 --> 00:14:14,645
As for the unreported case in Suwon,
she has no family.

225
00:14:14,728 --> 00:14:17,106
That's right.
That was probably why no one reported.

226
00:14:19,316 --> 00:14:21,026
What's going on?

227
00:14:21,569 --> 00:14:22,903
Don't tell meâ€¦

228
00:14:23,612 --> 00:14:24,572
No, right?

229
00:14:25,155 --> 00:14:27,324
Hey, I'm still new here.

230
00:14:27,408 --> 00:14:29,326
Isn't that why you got in touch with me?

231
00:14:30,035 --> 00:14:31,996
I'll go check the scene first.

232
00:14:32,079 --> 00:14:33,497
I'll go with you.

233
00:14:42,047 --> 00:14:43,173
Slowly.

234
00:14:51,223 --> 00:14:53,142
Inspector Song.

235
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:56,228
You came again.

236
00:14:57,062 --> 00:14:58,814
Yes. Here, it's just something small.

237
00:14:58,898 --> 00:15:00,983
My gosh, you always bring something.

238
00:15:01,066 --> 00:15:02,443
Where can I put this?

239
00:15:02,526 --> 00:15:03,861
You can put it over there.

240
00:15:04,361 --> 00:15:07,489
I'll leave you to talk. Since you're here,

241
00:15:07,573 --> 00:15:09,116
I should step out for lunch.

242
00:15:09,199 --> 00:15:11,785
You didn't have to come all the way here.

243
00:15:12,912 --> 00:15:15,164
I heard
you were undergoing rehabilitation.

244
00:15:15,247 --> 00:15:17,499
How are you feeling?

245
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:19,251
Not bad.

246
00:15:19,335 --> 00:15:21,462
Make yourselves at home.

247
00:15:21,545 --> 00:15:23,213
I'll leave you to talk.

248
00:15:23,297 --> 00:15:25,758
Please stay. We'll leave soon.

249
00:15:25,841 --> 00:15:28,594
You'll feel more comfortable without me.

250
00:15:28,677 --> 00:15:31,055
No, ma'am. That's not why we're here.

251
00:15:31,138 --> 00:15:32,222
Yes, just stay.

252
00:15:32,306 --> 00:15:35,893
I want to step out for lunch.

253
00:15:35,976 --> 00:15:39,897
-All right, then.
-Enjoy your lunch.

254
00:15:39,980 --> 00:15:41,231
Thank you.

255
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:44,485
Oh, let me.

256
00:15:49,073 --> 00:15:51,700
I can do it by myself. Thank you.

257
00:15:54,954 --> 00:15:56,914
You're doing much better now.

258
00:15:56,997 --> 00:15:59,667
Oh, we came to see you
when you were in the ICU.

259
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:02,211
That was when Captain Yoon and I
met your mother.

260
00:16:02,878 --> 00:16:04,672
Get better soon,

261
00:16:05,547 --> 00:16:07,341
so we can work together again.

262
00:16:08,008 --> 00:16:11,387
Yes, you're in high demand at the moment.

