00:32:15,350 --> 00:32:17,185
And handling this trash

525
00:32:18,353 --> 00:32:19,437
isn't easy.

526
00:32:19,520 --> 00:32:20,730
Right.

527
00:32:22,899 --> 00:32:24,609
And that probably exploded.

528
00:32:25,234 --> 00:32:27,779
He needs time to empty it out too.

529
00:32:29,781 --> 00:32:32,158
Time to empty it outâ€¦

530
00:32:32,784 --> 00:32:34,911
You need to take it easy too,
Captain Yoon.

531
00:32:35,703 --> 00:32:37,580
When people keep running without a break,

532
00:32:37,664 --> 00:32:39,999
they always trip over and explode.

533
00:32:41,709 --> 00:32:42,919
Soâ€¦

534
00:32:44,420 --> 00:32:47,924
what do you plan to do
about Inspector Song?

535
00:32:48,508 --> 00:32:49,634
I need to wait.

536
00:32:52,136 --> 00:32:53,805
After everything he's been through,

537
00:32:54,472 --> 00:32:55,932
I couldn't push him again

538
00:32:57,600 --> 00:32:59,143
because I felt responsible

539
00:33:01,229 --> 00:33:02,230
for his current state.

540
00:33:06,275 --> 00:33:07,527
PUNGYEON-DONG, ANYANG, GYEONGGI PROVINCE

541
00:33:11,030 --> 00:33:13,741
KARAOKE

542
00:33:17,662 --> 00:33:18,913
You're not going to sing?

543
00:33:20,915 --> 00:33:22,750
No. Let's just talk.

544
00:33:23,793 --> 00:33:24,919
It's a waste of money.

545
00:33:25,003 --> 00:33:26,170
Why don't you sing a song?

546
00:33:27,088 --> 00:33:28,548
I would rather talk to you

547
00:33:28,631 --> 00:33:31,092
than sing a song.

548
00:33:32,176 --> 00:33:34,470
Sure. I'll turn off the music.

549
00:33:41,519 --> 00:33:42,729
Shall we go for another round?

550
00:33:59,037 --> 00:34:01,456
-What are you doing?
-It's fine. Don't be like that.

551
00:34:01,539 --> 00:34:03,249
Stop it.

552
00:34:03,332 --> 00:34:04,625
Get your hands off me.

553
00:34:04,709 --> 00:34:05,960
Stop it!

554
00:34:06,044 --> 00:34:07,211
Damn it!

555
00:34:07,295 --> 00:34:09,047
What the hell are you doing?

556
00:34:11,549 --> 00:34:12,425
Hey.

557
00:34:13,134 --> 00:34:15,595
Open up. Unlock the door!

558
00:34:16,679 --> 00:34:18,347
Hey.

559
00:34:21,809 --> 00:34:22,810
You!

560
00:34:26,606 --> 00:34:29,067
You're ruining my good mood.

561
00:34:53,007 --> 00:34:55,051
GUKIL HOSPITAL

562
00:35:00,181 --> 00:35:01,015
SONG HA-YOUNG

563
00:35:05,353 --> 00:35:07,146
Excuse me.

564
00:35:07,688 --> 00:35:11,275
This is
Detective Song Ha-young's room, right?

565
00:35:12,360 --> 00:35:14,654
Yes, it is. Why do you ask?

566
00:35:14,737 --> 00:35:17,448
Could you give this to Detective Song?

567
00:35:18,157 --> 00:35:19,575
Sure.

568
00:35:23,204 --> 00:35:24,664
VOLUNTEER

569
00:35:31,504 --> 00:35:33,089
Hey, Ha-young.

570
00:35:33,172 --> 00:35:35,967
I think she works here as a volunteer.

571
00:35:36,050 --> 00:35:38,719
But she told me
to give this to you and left.

572
00:35:38,803 --> 00:35:40,138
A volunteer?

573
00:35:40,221 --> 00:35:42,265
Yes. Open it.
I'm curious to see what it is.

574
00:35:45,434 --> 00:35:47,937
Goodness. What's all this?

575
00:35:48,020 --> 00:35:50,523
She must be an excellent cook.

576
00:35:50,606 --> 00:35:53,151
Goodness. There's a card too.

577
00:35:53,234 --> 00:35:54,360
-Here.
-Right.

578
00:35:54,443 --> 00:35:57,071
Goodness. I can't believe this.

579
00:36:57,798 --> 00:37:01,802
<i>SOS. I can't handle
Chief Kook's jokes by myself.</i>

580
00:37:01,886 --> 00:37:03,888
<i>I hope you get well and come back soon.</i>

581
00:37:03,971 --> 00:37:05,765
<i>How's the rehab going?</i>

582
00:37:05,848 --> 00:37:08,851
<i>I'm sorry for not visiting you often.</i>

583
00:37:08,935 --> 00:37:11,562
<i>Inspector Song, it's winter now.</i>

584
00:37:11,646 --> 00:37:13,481
<i>It's gotten cold.</i>

585
00:37:13,564 --> 00:37:16,525
<i>Don't catch a cold,
and take care of yourself.</i>

586
00:37:21,072 --> 00:37:23,449
RESIGNATION LETTER

587
00:37:29,372 --> 00:37:30,581
INVESTIGATIVE POINTS

588
00:37:30,665 --> 00:37:32,291
THE SUSPECT LIVES ALONE

589
00:37:43,678 --> 00:37:45,054
<i>Think only about the victimsâ€¦</i>

590
00:37:45,763 --> 00:37:47,598
<i>and the bereaved families.</i>

591
00:37:47,682 --> 00:37:51,060
TOJUNG-DONG, ANYANG, GYEONGGI PROVINCE

592
00:38:25,469 --> 00:38:28,180
Sir, I want to touch that!

593
00:38:29,640 --> 00:38:30,683
Which one? That one?

594
00:38:30,766 --> 00:38:32,226
That one over there.

595
00:38:32,810 --> 00:38:34,103
Come here.

596
00:38:35,438 --> 00:38:36,981
How pretty.

597
00:38:38,316 --> 00:38:39,692
Is that all?

598
00:38:39,775 --> 00:38:42,361
-No. I want to touch this too!
-This one?

599
00:38:52,163 --> 00:38:53,581
-Right?
-Yes.

600
00:39:01,714 --> 00:39:02,840
EMERGENCY MEDICAL CENTER

601
00:39:02,923 --> 00:39:04,800
You seem to be doing much better now.

602
00:39:04,884 --> 00:39:06,510
Yes, thanks to you.

603
00:39:07,303 --> 00:39:08,637
That's good to hear.

604
00:39:09,805 --> 00:39:11,390
Thank you for the food.

605
00:39:11,932 --> 00:39:13,309
I really enjoyed it.

606
00:39:14,352 --> 00:39:15,561
I should've thanked you sooner.

607
00:39:16,270 --> 00:39:17,813
It was long ago,

608
00:39:18,481 --> 00:39:20,608
so I didn't think you'd remember me

609
00:39:21,275 --> 00:39:23,819
since you work on so many cases.

610
00:39:24,403 --> 00:39:25,613
I remember everything.

611
00:39:27,073 --> 00:39:28,449
I remember Ms. Choi Hwa-yeonâ€¦

612
00:39:31,077 --> 00:39:32,328
and you too.

613
00:39:38,626 --> 00:39:39,627
It's just that

614
00:39:42,463 --> 00:39:44,173
I didn't have the courage.

615
00:39:46,008 --> 00:39:46,967
To faceâ€¦

616
00:39:47,676 --> 00:39:48,928
the victims

617
00:39:50,054 --> 00:39:52,181
or their families again.

618
00:39:54,308 --> 00:39:55,643
I felt the same way.

619
00:40:00,898 --> 00:40:04,110
When I think about the scumbag
who did that to Hwa-yeon,

620
00:40:04,819 --> 00:40:06,946
I still want him to suffer the same.

621
00:40:08,489 --> 00:40:10,991
Whenever I'm reminded that
he's doing just fine in jail,

622
00:40:11,075 --> 00:40:12,576
I feel so resentful.

623
00:40:13,494 --> 00:40:15,663
I just want to follow Hwa-yeon
and die too.

624
00:40:20,334 --> 00:40:22,002
My life has been so miserable.

625
00:40:24,338 --> 00:40:26,590
To tell you the truth,
I couldn't bring myself

626
00:40:26,674 --> 00:40:29,385
to say hello to you
when I first saw you here

627
00:40:29,885 --> 00:40:32,680
because all the horrible memories
came rushing back.

628
00:40:33,973 --> 00:40:36,684
I had nightmares for days.

629
00:40:38,644 --> 00:40:40,896
I thought maybe I should stop

630
00:40:40,980 --> 00:40:42,481
volunteering here.

631
00:40:44,984 --> 00:40:45,985
I'm sorry.

632
00:40:47,111 --> 00:40:48,821
Why are you sorry?

633
00:40:49,864 --> 00:40:52,116
I should thank you if anything.

634
00:41:02,877 --> 00:41:05,546
That's why I still had the handkerchief.

635
00:41:06,964 --> 00:41:09,675
One day, I saw it again

636
00:41:10,468 --> 00:41:12,052
and realized

637
00:41:13,721 --> 00:41:16,682
that I had been able to hold out

638
00:41:18,184 --> 00:41:19,393
thanks to everyone

639
00:41:19,477 --> 00:41:21,979
who did their best for me and Hwa-yeon.

640
00:41:25,649 --> 00:41:28,027
And you're one of them.

641
00:41:31,739 --> 00:41:32,823
Hold on a moment.

642
00:41:33,449 --> 00:41:35,409
-Where are you going?
-I'll be right back.

643
00:41:35,493 --> 00:41:36,827
Just a moment.

644
00:41:41,832 --> 00:41:43,834
I ran into you,
so I couldn't prepare anything

645
00:41:43,918 --> 00:41:46,003
Here, take this and eat it.

646
00:41:46,086 --> 00:41:47,296
No, it's okay.

647
00:41:47,379 --> 00:41:49,298
I bought it just now, so it's still warm.

648
00:41:49,381 --> 00:41:50,716
Then let's eat it together.

649
00:41:50,799 --> 00:41:52,551
This is for your recovery

650
00:41:52,635 --> 00:41:54,261
and a small token of my gratitude.

651
00:41:57,973 --> 00:41:59,517
I read the newspaper articles.

652
00:42:00,601 --> 00:42:02,186
Just like back then,

653
00:42:02,269 --> 00:42:05,356
you only think about
the victims and their families.

654
00:42:06,357 --> 00:42:08,442
<i>-Thank you very much.
-No problem.</i>

655
00:42:09,193 --> 00:42:12,321
<i>Some of the bereaved manage
to pluck up the courage to live on,</i>

656
00:42:13,447 --> 00:42:16,617
<i>but I'm sure some are
still drowning in sorrow.</i>

657
00:42:19,703 --> 00:42:22,414
Please help people like us,

658
00:42:23,832 --> 00:42:25,376
so no one else

659
00:42:26,585 --> 00:42:28,671
has to lose their loved ones like that.

660
00:43:10,588 --> 00:43:14,550
<i>Joy to the world, the Lord has come</i>

661
00:43:50,085 --> 00:43:51,629
-Inspector Song!
-Hey.

662
00:43:53,714 --> 00:43:55,716
-You woke him up.
-I'm sorry.

663
00:43:57,468 --> 00:43:59,678
It's okay. I had to get up anyway.

664
00:43:59,762 --> 00:44:02,181
-When did you get here?
-Just now.

665
00:44:02,264 --> 00:44:03,682
Here, this is for you.

666
00:44:03,766 --> 00:44:05,893
I picked out the best ones.

667
00:44:05,976 --> 00:44:06,935
Thank you.

668
00:44:08,646 --> 00:44:10,230
When will Chief Kook get here?

669
00:44:10,314 --> 00:44:11,649
I thought he was coming with you.

670
00:44:12,775 --> 00:44:14,026
He'll be here later.

671
00:44:14,818 --> 00:44:16,487
-Have some.
-Thank you.

672
00:44:17,404 --> 00:44:19,698
-You too, Reporter Choi.
-Thank you.

673
00:44:19,782 --> 00:44:21,158
You can go home soon, right?

674
00:44:22,618 --> 00:44:23,494
Yes, in two days.

675
00:44:23,577 --> 00:44:25,037
After almost six months.

676
00:44:25,120 --> 00:44:27,289
-How do you feel?
-Is this an interview?

677
00:44:27,373 --> 00:44:28,957
Come up with better questions.

678
00:44:29,041 --> 00:44:30,834
Of course, he's excited.

679
00:44:30,918 --> 00:44:33,212
Then what will you do
as soon as you get home?

680
00:44:34,129 --> 00:44:35,130
I'm not sure.

681
00:44:36,465 --> 00:44:38,217
I haven't really thought about it.

682
00:44:45,849 --> 00:44:49,019
Wait, hold on!

683
00:45:01,907 --> 00:45:03,200
Let's go eat something.

684
00:45:03,283 --> 00:45:04,368
You want to eat again?

685
00:45:04,451 --> 00:45:05,577
You didn't have dinner?

686
00:45:05,661 --> 00:45:07,663
I did, but I'm hungry again.

687
00:45:07,746 --> 00:45:09,873
-It's winter, you know.
-She eats a lot.

688
00:45:09,957 --> 00:45:12,793
-It's good to eat a lot.
-Oh, Chief Kook.

689
00:45:13,585 --> 00:45:15,629
-You made it.
-We waited for you until now.

690
00:45:15,712 --> 00:45:17,840
-I see. You're leaving now?
-Yes, we are.

691
00:45:18,465 --> 00:45:19,758
You're here.

692
00:45:20,592 --> 00:45:21,802
Hey.

693
00:45:21,885 --> 00:45:22,970
Get in, guys.

694
00:45:24,596 --> 00:45:27,224
I guess these guys kept you up.
You should be in bed now.

695
00:45:27,307 --> 00:45:29,393
You just got here.
Are you leaving right away?

696
00:45:30,894 --> 00:45:31,770
Yes. I mean, no.

697
00:45:35,732 --> 00:45:38,569
Actually, I should get going.
You need to go to bed.

698
00:45:38,652 --> 00:45:41,238
I'm glad to see you looking healthy.
I'll be off, then.

699
00:45:41,321 --> 00:45:42,489
Bye.

700
00:45:43,073 --> 00:45:45,242
-See you in the office.
-Okay, good night.

701
00:45:53,000 --> 00:45:55,461
What did Ha-young say just now?

702
00:45:55,544 --> 00:45:56,879
"See you in the office."

703
00:46:08,765 --> 00:46:09,808
What is it?

704
00:46:21,820 --> 00:46:24,239
Excuse me, did you miss the bus just now?

705
00:46:24,823 --> 00:46:26,700
-Pardon?
-It's cold.

706
00:46:26,783 --> 00:46:28,368
I can give you a ride.

707
00:46:28,952 --> 00:46:32,080
I'm following the bus route anyway,

708
00:46:32,164 --> 00:46:36,001
so I can drop you off along the way.

709
00:46:43,675 --> 00:46:45,886
-This looks so good.
-It looks amazing.

710
00:46:48,972 --> 00:46:51,266
Eat it with green onions. It's so good.

711
00:46:54,895 --> 00:46:56,355
Inspector Song

712
00:46:56,438 --> 00:46:58,815
looked more high-spirited
than ever before.

713
00:46:58,899 --> 00:47:01,902
I'm sure he's relieved
that he can finally go home.

714
00:47:01,985 --> 00:47:03,529
It must've been tough.

715
00:47:05,989 --> 00:47:07,908
Oh, Detective Nam.

716
00:47:07,991 --> 00:47:09,660
What are you doing here?

717
00:47:10,661 --> 00:47:13,997
We met at Mapo Police Station
and in front of Seoul HQ as well.

718
00:47:14,081 --> 00:47:15,707
You remember me, right?

719
00:47:15,791 --> 00:47:17,918
I'm Reporter Choi Yoon-ji from Fact Today.

720
00:47:18,835 --> 00:47:20,796
That's right, Reporter Choi Yoon-ji.

721
00:47:20,879 --> 00:47:22,506
I'm Nam Il-young,
Wide-Area Investigation Squad.

722
00:47:22,589 --> 00:47:25,509
-Good to see you.
-You're always so quick.

723
00:47:25,592 --> 00:47:27,970
-Are you here alone?
-I stopped by on my way home.

724
00:47:28,053 --> 00:47:30,138
I'm picking up my late-night snack.

725
00:47:30,639 --> 00:47:31,932
-Let's sit down.
-Okay.

726
00:47:32,015 --> 00:47:34,893
-We were going to order some drinks.
-I see.

727
00:47:34,977 --> 00:47:37,688
Excuse me, could we get two more servings?

728
00:47:37,771 --> 00:47:38,605
My goodness.

729
00:47:38,689 --> 00:47:41,275
I don't want to be a third wheel.

730
00:47:41,358 --> 00:47:43,443
Gosh, no. We're just friends.

731
00:47:43,527 --> 00:47:46,780
-Don't even worry about it.
-Oh, really?

732
00:47:46,863 --> 00:47:48,782
You sure know
how to enjoy beef intestines.

733
00:47:59,418 --> 00:48:01,295
BUS STOP
GEUMCHAN VILLAGE

734
00:48:04,965 --> 00:48:06,133
Thank you.

735
00:48:07,509 --> 00:48:10,470
Were you out with your friends?

736
00:48:10,554 --> 00:48:12,681
Yes.

737
00:48:13,599 --> 00:48:16,101
I couldn't just pass by,
looking at you freezing.

738
00:48:16,184 --> 00:48:17,060
Thank you.

739
00:48:17,144 --> 00:48:18,937
You can just drop me off along the way.

740
00:48:19,938 --> 00:48:21,523
It'll probably start snowing soon.

741
00:48:21,607 --> 00:48:23,442
We should help each other out, you know?

742
00:48:24,943 --> 00:48:28,447
Who knows? Santa Claus may give us a gift.

743
00:48:29,072 --> 00:48:30,240
That's true.

744
00:48:30,324 --> 00:48:32,826
You deserve
a nice Christmas gift for this.

745
00:48:34,536 --> 00:48:36,246
Then how about you give me a gift?

746
00:48:39,041 --> 00:48:40,042
Sorry?

747
00:48:42,085 --> 00:48:43,211
I want a gift.

748
00:49:05,734 --> 00:49:06,860
Hey.

749
00:49:08,403 --> 00:49:10,280
I had fun thanks to you.

750
00:49:16,620 --> 00:49:19,623
{\an8}CHIEF PARK DAE-WOONG

751
00:49:19,706 --> 00:49:20,666
Hello?

752
00:49:24,127 --> 00:49:25,253
Okay.

753
00:49:31,301 --> 00:49:32,344
Superintendent Heo.

754
00:49:32,427 --> 00:49:35,764
Another girl has gone missing
in Tojung-dong.

755
00:49:36,431 --> 00:49:39,768
-Again?
-I think it's the same guy.

756
00:49:42,646 --> 00:49:44,022
Give Young-soo a call too.

757
00:49:44,106 --> 00:49:46,233
FEMALE COLLEGE STUDENT GOES MISSING
IN GYEONGGI PROVINCE BEFORE CHRISTMAS

758
00:49:47,275 --> 00:49:48,652
-Chief.
-Yes?

759
00:49:48,735 --> 00:49:51,488
We received a missing person's report
from Tojung-dong, right?

760
00:49:51,571 --> 00:49:52,781
Yes. Why do you ask?

761
00:49:57,119 --> 00:49:58,328
Yes, Chief Park?

762
00:49:59,621 --> 00:50:02,290
Okay. I got it.
I'm going to Gyeonggi Agency.

763
00:50:02,374 --> 00:50:03,709
Okay, I'll see you later.

764
00:50:04,334 --> 00:50:06,253
Yes, I'll head over right now.

765
00:50:06,336 --> 00:50:08,588
-Here's your receipt.
-Oh, yes.

766
00:50:08,672 --> 00:50:10,257
Thank you.

767
00:50:14,344 --> 00:50:16,304
I'll get a taxi for you. Go home first.

768
00:50:16,388 --> 00:50:18,807
Don't do that, I can take the bus.

769
00:50:18,890 --> 00:50:20,350
Taxis are more comfortable.

770
00:50:21,143 --> 00:50:22,644
All right, then. Thank you.

771
00:50:22,728 --> 00:50:24,646
Take it easy, okay?

772
00:50:24,730 --> 00:50:26,022
Yes, don't worry.

773
00:50:26,106 --> 00:50:28,859
I'm so glad you're getting discharged.

774
00:50:28,942 --> 00:50:31,027
I won't scare you like that again.
I'm sorry.

775
00:50:31,111 --> 00:50:32,654
-Let me carry that.
-It's fine.

776
00:50:32,738 --> 00:50:34,322
-I got it.
-You're so stubborn.

777
00:50:34,406 --> 00:50:36,324
-I told you to take it easy.
-Let's go.

778
00:50:40,829 --> 00:50:43,415
SEOUL METROPOLITAN POLICE AGENCY

779
00:50:45,208 --> 00:50:46,334
Inspector.

780
00:50:47,169 --> 00:50:49,880
-Are you feeling better?
-Yes, I'm fine.

781
00:50:49,963 --> 00:50:52,090
Why did you come here
instead of heading home?

782
00:50:52,174 --> 00:50:53,759
I'm good to work now.

783
00:50:54,968 --> 00:50:55,886
Where's Chief Kook?

784
00:50:55,969 --> 00:50:57,512
He went to the Gyeonggi Agency.

785
00:50:58,847 --> 00:51:00,140
The Gyeonggi Police Agency?

786
00:51:01,016 --> 00:51:02,517
Why did he go there?

787
00:51:13,779 --> 00:51:18,366
TRUSTWORTHY POLICE
SAFE AND STRONG COUNTRY

788
00:51:18,992 --> 00:51:22,245
There was a bus stop
in front of the karaoke bar, right?

789
00:51:22,329 --> 00:51:24,414
-Yes, there was.
-Okay.

790
00:51:24,498 --> 00:51:27,918
The missing person's job group
is completely different though.

791
00:51:28,001 --> 00:51:30,086
But the area is all very similar.

792
00:51:34,674 --> 00:51:36,384
Hey, how did you know I was here?

793
00:51:36,468 --> 00:51:38,053
Are you feeling better?

794
00:51:39,179 --> 00:51:40,472
Yes.

795
00:51:41,181 --> 00:51:43,975
-It's been a while.
-Have you been well?

796
00:51:48,814 --> 00:51:51,441
Woo-ju briefed me on the case
when I got to the office.

797
00:51:51,525 --> 00:51:53,401
Can you explain the case to me in detail?

798
00:51:53,485 --> 00:51:56,738
All right. As it was reported here,

799
00:51:56,822 --> 00:51:59,616
a woman went missing
from a karaoke bar in April.

800
00:51:59,699 --> 00:52:01,451
But back in February,

801
00:52:01,535 --> 00:52:03,203
another employee from a karaoke bar

802
00:52:03,286 --> 00:52:05,288
went missing but it wasn't reported.

803
00:52:05,372 --> 00:52:07,123
Then two days ago, on the 23rd,

804
00:52:07,207 --> 00:52:10,627
a female university student went missing
from the same bus stop.

805
00:52:10,710 --> 00:52:13,004
I think it's the same perp
for all three cases.

806
00:52:13,088 --> 00:52:16,967
When we visited the crime scene
for the case in April,

807
00:52:17,050 --> 00:52:18,635
there was a bus stop there too.

808
00:52:18,718 --> 00:52:20,220
What about the unreported case?

809
00:52:20,303 --> 00:52:22,055
There was a bus stop there too.

810
00:52:23,306 --> 00:52:26,017
All three cases happened
in a desolate area.

811
00:52:28,270 --> 00:52:29,563
He's looking at the location.

812
00:52:30,647 --> 00:52:32,315
You figured that out already?

813
00:52:37,028 --> 00:52:38,488
No witnesses, right?

814
00:52:38,572 --> 00:52:39,614
That's right.

815
00:52:39,698 --> 00:52:42,784
So if we take Chief Kook's guess
and assume that all three

816
00:52:42,868 --> 00:52:44,369
were abducted from a bus stopâ€¦

817
00:52:44,452 --> 00:52:46,413
That means they were waiting for the bus.

818
00:52:46,496 --> 00:52:47,539
What time did this happen?

819
00:52:47,622 --> 00:52:51,001
All of their phones went radio silent
around 1 a.m. in the morning.

820
00:52:52,252 --> 00:52:53,587
They were waiting for the last bus.

821
00:52:55,005 --> 00:52:57,007
He might have forced them into the car.

822
00:52:57,090 --> 00:53:00,385
Don't you need at least two people
to force an adult into your car?

823
00:53:01,595 --> 00:53:03,179
They were offered a free ride.

824
00:53:03,263 --> 00:53:05,390
-What?
-A free ride, you say.

825
00:53:05,473 --> 00:53:07,851
If there are two culprits,
there's no good reason

826
00:53:07,934 --> 00:53:09,352
to abduct women at a bus stop.

827
00:53:09,436 --> 00:53:12,981
They can just target a woman walking alone
and abduct her by force.

828
00:53:16,234 --> 00:53:19,571
I think there's a high chance
that it's the same culprit.

829
00:53:21,114 --> 00:53:23,033
-Chief Park.
-Yes?

830
00:53:23,950 --> 00:53:25,452
Let's form an investigation team.

831
00:53:26,119 --> 00:53:29,039
{\an8}GYEONGGI INVESTIGATION HEADQUARTERS
OF SERIAL MISSING WOMEN CASE

832
00:53:29,122 --> 00:53:30,665
JANUARY 2007

833
00:53:36,922 --> 00:53:38,882
Let us in on the investigation too.

834
00:53:41,301 --> 00:53:44,679
We have experience
working with the Analysis Team.

835
00:53:44,763 --> 00:53:46,890
I'm sure we'll come in handy.

836
00:53:48,516 --> 00:53:49,935
All right, fine.

837
00:53:50,018 --> 00:53:52,771
I'll ask the Gyeonggi Agency
for permission to cooperate.

838
00:53:54,022 --> 00:53:55,440
-Thank you, sir.
-All right.

839
00:53:56,524 --> 00:53:59,277
You'll be working at the
Gyeonggi Agency for a while, right?

840
00:53:59,361 --> 00:54:00,862
Yes, probably.

841
00:54:01,947 --> 00:54:03,114
Hold on.

842
00:54:06,242 --> 00:54:08,286
Hey, what should I do with this?

843
00:54:08,370 --> 00:54:09,788
Should I rip it up?

844
00:54:09,871 --> 00:54:10,830
RESIGNATION LETTER

845
00:54:10,914 --> 00:54:12,457
-Come on.
-Should I?

846
00:54:15,001 --> 00:54:16,378
You're so twisted.

847
00:54:18,588 --> 00:54:20,966
Woo-ju. Rip that up into pieces
once we leave.

848
00:54:21,049 --> 00:54:22,342
I'll do as you command.

849
00:54:22,425 --> 00:54:24,427
-I'm counting on you, Woo-ju.
-Sure thing.

850
00:54:24,511 --> 00:54:26,137
"Woo-ju," please?

851
00:54:26,221 --> 00:54:29,808
GYEONGGI PROVINCIAL POLICE AGENCY

852
00:54:30,392 --> 00:54:32,519
-Let's get started then.
-Yes, sir.

853
00:54:33,353 --> 00:54:34,771
{\an8}MISSING WOMEN CASES IN GYEONGGI

854
00:54:37,065 --> 00:54:39,025
There were no security cameras
at the scene.

855
00:54:39,109 --> 00:54:41,069
Most of those areas don't have any.

856
00:54:41,152 --> 00:54:43,530
They're building
new apartment complexes there.

857
00:54:43,613 --> 00:54:46,741
The district office didn't even look
for installation spots.

858
00:54:46,825 --> 00:54:49,411
The culprit knows
the area is pretty desolate

859
00:54:49,494 --> 00:54:50,662
with no security cameras.

860
00:54:50,745 --> 00:54:53,707
I think we should install security cameras
not just in this area,

861
00:54:53,790 --> 00:54:56,835
but also at every bus stop
with no security cameras in Gyeonggi.

862
00:54:56,918 --> 00:55:00,255
-Every single one?
-Yes, switch out the old ones too.

863
00:55:00,338 --> 00:55:03,174
You can barely make out license plates
with the older models.

864
00:55:03,258 --> 00:55:06,261
You think it's that simple?

865
00:55:06,344 --> 00:55:07,929
The Ministry of Finance has toâ€¦

866
00:55:09,806 --> 00:55:11,016
Fine. I'll talk to them.

867
00:55:11,099 --> 00:55:13,935
Then I'll check for areas
with no security cameras.

868
00:55:14,019 --> 00:55:16,187
-All right.
-Thanks, I appreciate it.

869
00:55:22,986 --> 00:55:25,113
A SAFE COUNTRY WITH HAPPY CITIZENS
A COUNTRY OF SECURITY POWER

870
00:55:28,533 --> 00:55:29,659
Have you been well?

871
00:55:30,702 --> 00:55:32,037
Yes, thanks to you.

872
00:55:33,705 --> 00:55:35,165
Thanks to me?

873
00:55:35,248 --> 00:55:38,877
You played a part in my
joining the Analysis Team.

874
00:55:40,962 --> 00:55:42,338
I see you can make jokes now.

875
00:55:42,922 --> 00:55:46,468
The rumors about Chief Kook
whipping you into shape was true.

876
00:55:47,052 --> 00:55:48,845
Yes, he sure did.

877
00:55:48,928 --> 00:55:51,139
I was appointed to a new station
so suddenly,

878
00:55:51,848 --> 00:55:52,974
so I couldn't reach out.

879
00:55:54,267 --> 00:55:56,519
Anyone would've done the same thing.

880
00:55:58,104 --> 00:55:59,397
It's all in the past now.

881
00:56:00,273 --> 00:56:01,733
I'm just glad we met again.

882
00:56:04,652 --> 00:56:05,695
Let's do our best.

883
00:56:19,209 --> 00:56:22,045
Did you hear the rumors
about you whipping me into shape?

884
00:56:22,128 --> 00:56:25,507
What kind of absolute nonsense is that?

885
00:56:25,590 --> 00:56:27,717
Who whipped who into what?

886
00:56:27,801 --> 00:56:29,260
People just love to gossip.

887
00:56:30,136 --> 00:56:31,221
What's wrong with it?

888
00:56:32,138 --> 00:56:34,599
Don't let rumors bother you.

889
00:56:37,310 --> 00:56:38,770
It's true though.

890
00:56:40,772 --> 00:56:43,608
The buses run in
40 to 50-minute intervals.

891
00:56:43,691 --> 00:56:44,692
That's quite a wait.

892
00:56:45,276 --> 00:56:47,904
Right. There aren't many taxis either.

893
00:56:48,988 --> 00:56:50,198
Even more so at night.

894
00:56:50,281 --> 00:56:51,783
He probably had that in mind.

895
00:56:52,826 --> 00:56:55,245
The security camera installation
is finalized, right?

896
00:56:55,328 --> 00:56:57,789
Yes. They'll install more
in the areas of disappearance

897
00:56:57,872 --> 00:56:59,541
and all nearby locations.

898
00:57:10,468 --> 00:57:11,803
SINBON 2-DONG OFFICE

899
00:57:17,767 --> 00:57:19,185
I hope the cameras help.

900
00:57:19,269 --> 00:57:22,230
I'm sure he'll be more cautious
with the lack of blind spots.

901
00:57:23,106 --> 00:57:24,816
It's been over nine months now.

902
00:57:25,483 --> 00:57:26,985
I hope they are alive.

903
00:57:27,861 --> 00:57:31,114
At least none of the missing women
were found dead.

904
00:57:32,198 --> 00:57:33,408
Yes, you're right.

905
00:57:34,284 --> 00:57:35,410
We should be hopeful.

906
00:57:36,703 --> 00:57:37,829
Let's go over there.

907
00:57:56,973 --> 00:57:59,309
He's the statistical analyst
of the Analysis Team.

908
00:57:59,392 --> 00:58:02,020
His name is Jung Woo-ju. He's a smart guy.

909
00:58:02,103 --> 00:58:03,229
My name is Yoon Tae-gu.

910
00:58:04,022 --> 00:58:05,398
I'll leave.

911
00:58:07,901 --> 00:58:11,279
Did you have customers
who offered to give people a ride?

912
00:58:11,362 --> 00:58:14,032
BUS STOP

913
00:58:14,115 --> 00:58:15,658
It's cold. Hop in.

914
00:58:15,742 --> 00:58:17,785
-I'll take you to the main street.
-Right.

915
00:58:20,497 --> 00:58:21,831
SUSPECT ANALYSIS

916
00:58:21,915 --> 00:58:23,041
PROFILING REPORT

917
00:58:23,124 --> 00:58:24,667
GYEONGGI INVESTIGATION HEADQUARTERS
OF SERIAL MISSING WOMEN CASE

918
00:58:24,751 --> 00:58:27,504
All three cases broke out
when the wind chill factor was low.

919
00:58:27,587 --> 00:58:30,548
It was a secluded area,
so buses didn't come often.

920
00:58:30,632 --> 00:58:32,592
I stood alone at the bus stop,

921
00:58:32,675 --> 00:58:35,887
<i>but a truck came by and offered me a ride
out into the main street.</i>

922
00:58:36,387 --> 00:58:38,515
You won't find a bus here
even if you waited.

923
00:58:38,598 --> 00:58:41,309
The culprit takes advantage
of the victim's situation and psychology.

924
00:58:41,392 --> 00:58:42,894
The buses don't run often,

925
00:58:42,977 --> 00:58:45,063
so it's common for people to give rides

926
00:58:45,146 --> 00:58:46,981
in that neighborhood.

927
00:58:47,065 --> 00:58:50,360
On a cold day, it must've been easier.

928
00:58:50,443 --> 00:58:54,030
So the culprit used the kind face
as a mask to lure them?

929
00:58:54,614 --> 00:58:55,490
Yes.

930
00:58:55,573 --> 00:58:59,369
Even so, how can they gladly
hop into a stranger's car?

931
00:58:59,452 --> 00:59:00,703
They didn't hop in gladly.

932
00:59:01,704 --> 00:59:03,748
The culprit must've
convinced them to hop in.

933
00:59:03,831 --> 00:59:07,460
Then the culprit must drive
a luxurious sedan that seems familiar.

934
00:59:07,544 --> 00:59:11,256
Or have something in his car
that drives away people's suspicion.

935
00:59:11,339 --> 00:59:14,050
A family photo? Or stuffed animals?

936
00:59:15,343 --> 00:59:18,304
-A baby?
-Let's say a baby is in the car.

937
00:59:18,388 --> 00:59:21,140
Then people rarely
ask anybody else to join them.

938
00:59:21,224 --> 00:59:23,935
The first thing
the victim looks at is the driver.

939
00:59:24,686 --> 00:59:26,938
So I think the suspect may look amicable,

940
00:59:27,021 --> 00:59:29,148
someone who doesn't draw
people's suspicion.

941
00:59:29,232 --> 00:59:31,276
I'm sure the culprit isn't intimidating.

942
00:59:31,359 --> 00:59:32,485
Must be likable.

943
00:59:33,820 --> 00:59:34,862
You're right.

944
00:59:38,950 --> 00:59:40,034
Hello? Chief Kook.

945
00:59:40,118 --> 00:59:42,203
I'll send you a fax.
Please take a look at it.

946
00:59:43,121 --> 00:59:44,914
Yes, a cold case for a missing person.

947
00:59:46,916 --> 00:59:47,834
Yes, in Gunpo.

948
00:59:47,917 --> 00:59:49,294
GUNPO

949
00:59:49,377 --> 00:59:51,504
Yes, I'll check.

950
00:59:53,506 --> 00:59:54,716
One second.

951
00:59:54,799 --> 00:59:56,843
Woo-ju just sent over
a missing person case.

952
00:59:56,926 --> 01:00:01,347
The victim is Heo Geum-young,
51 years old, who went missing in Gunpo.

953
01:00:01,431 --> 01:00:02,432
And is it similar?

954
01:00:02,515 --> 01:00:03,891
She went missing

955
01:00:03,975 --> 01:00:06,269
at a bus stop in a secluded area.

956
01:00:06,352 --> 01:00:09,522
Her phone battery got separated
around that area.

957
01:00:10,106 --> 01:00:10,940
Seems possible.

958
01:00:11,024 --> 01:00:13,234
-He sent us a fax.
-I'll pick it up.

959
01:00:13,318 --> 01:00:14,360
No, I got it.

960
01:00:14,444 --> 01:00:15,653
I'm going to the restroom.

961
01:00:17,697 --> 01:00:20,158
-She was 51 years old?
-Yes.

962
01:00:24,412 --> 01:00:25,330
Hey.

963
01:00:25,413 --> 01:00:28,458
We just heard
about the cold case in Gunpo--

964
01:00:32,587 --> 01:00:34,422
Yes. One second.

965
01:00:34,505 --> 01:00:36,049
Hey, don't hang up.

966
01:00:37,175 --> 01:00:38,885
It's a word on a missing case.

967
01:00:38,968 --> 01:00:41,638
No, not the Gunpo cold case.
Not that one. Something else.

968
01:00:43,181 --> 01:00:44,599
Suwon Seobu Police Station.

969
01:00:44,682 --> 01:00:46,017
An office worker, in her thirties.

970
01:00:46,100 --> 01:00:48,936
<i>That neighborhood recently
became filled with industrial parks.</i>

971
01:00:49,020 --> 01:00:51,439
<i>The missing person worked in
Haeyong Industrial Park.</i>

972
01:00:52,065 --> 01:00:54,108
<i>She usually commuted by bus
at the bus stop</i>

973
01:00:54,192 --> 01:00:55,485
<i>in front of her workplace.</i>

974
01:00:55,568 --> 01:00:58,196
<i>That area only has
industrial parks around,</i>

975
01:00:58,279 --> 01:01:00,615
<i>so everything is pitch dark at night.</i>

976
01:01:01,199 --> 01:01:03,618
<i>Her phone battery was pulled out
at 7 a.m. the next morning.</i>

977
01:01:04,494 --> 01:01:05,953
MISSING PERSON

978
01:01:20,343 --> 01:01:23,721
A HILL IN ANSAN, GYEONGGI PROVINCE

979
01:02:04,345 --> 01:02:05,430
Hello, Chief Park?

980
01:02:05,513 --> 01:02:07,265
We found Yoon Jin-sil's body.

981
01:02:07,849 --> 01:02:09,809
The karaoke bar employee
who went missing in January.

982
01:02:09,892 --> 01:02:11,477
Did you see the news?

983
01:02:11,561 --> 01:02:14,105
She went missing,
then was found buried in secret.

984
01:02:14,731 --> 01:02:16,524
I should check on my wife.

985
01:02:16,607 --> 01:02:17,900
That's horrendous.

986
01:02:17,984 --> 01:02:19,318
{\an8}MISSING KARAOKE BAR EMPLOYEE
IN HER THIRTIES, FOUND DEAD IN ANSAN

987
01:02:29,871 --> 01:02:31,164
Get up here!

988
01:02:35,376 --> 01:02:36,252
Go up!

989
01:02:36,335 --> 01:02:38,838
Something might come out,
so keep digging up there!

990
01:02:38,921 --> 01:02:40,047
Yes!

991
01:02:43,509 --> 01:02:45,720
{\an8}FOUND NAKED
WITH STOCKINGS TIED AROUND THE NECK

992
01:02:50,850 --> 01:02:53,603
GYEONGGI PROVINCIAL POLICE AGENCY

993
01:02:53,686 --> 01:02:57,023
Ansan is pretty far
from the last phone signal

994
01:02:57,106 --> 01:02:58,524
and where she went missing.

995
01:02:58,608 --> 01:02:59,984
You're right.

996
01:03:00,067 --> 01:03:01,694
Why didn't he go near Anyang?

997
01:03:01,778 --> 01:03:05,990
I'm not sure why he went
all the way to Ansan to bury her.

998
01:03:06,073 --> 01:03:09,452
The farther one travels,
the riskier it becomes.

999
01:03:09,535 --> 01:03:11,829
He probably didn't make a move by day.

1000
01:03:12,413 --> 01:03:14,499
He went around at night
when it was difficult

1001
01:03:14,582 --> 01:03:16,000
to spot his car on camera.

1002
01:03:16,083 --> 01:03:17,960
He either lived in Gyeonggi
for a long time,

1003
01:03:19,212 --> 01:03:21,005
or he must know the area well.

1004
01:03:21,589 --> 01:03:22,965
Gimpo, Anyang, Suwon, and Ansan.

1005
01:03:23,049 --> 01:03:25,176
He usually found the most secluded areas.

1006
01:03:25,259 --> 01:03:28,012
Lots of places don't show up
on GPS in that area.

1007
01:03:28,095 --> 01:03:30,139
You're right, on top of that,
he buried her

1008
01:03:30,223 --> 01:03:32,141
in a hill 80m away from the road.

1009
01:03:32,975 --> 01:03:34,769
If it hadn't been for that elderly man

1010
01:03:34,852 --> 01:03:36,521
who goes there every day,

1011
01:03:36,604 --> 01:03:39,398
it would've been impossible
for an ordinary person to spot.

1012
01:03:39,482 --> 01:03:40,817
Then let's find the cars

1013
01:03:40,900 --> 01:03:42,109
that we can distinguish

1014
01:03:42,193 --> 01:03:43,569
from the security footage.

1015
01:03:44,612 --> 01:03:45,863
We have no choice

1016
01:03:45,947 --> 01:03:49,116
but to narrow down our suspects
to ex-convicts living in Gyeonggi.

1017
01:03:49,951 --> 01:03:52,161
There must be a reason
why he chose this spot.

1018
01:03:53,913 --> 01:03:56,541
Once we find some suspects,
we'll also find the reason.

1019
01:03:56,624 --> 01:03:59,126
Detective Nam.
Put together a list of ex-convicts.

1020
01:03:59,210 --> 01:04:00,253
Yes, sir.

1021
01:04:47,508 --> 01:04:48,843
AN YU-YEON

